Method Detail

getAnnotationValues

java.util.Set<java.lang.Object> getAnnotationValues(java.lang.String property)
For a single annotation property (i.e. a predicate), multiple annotation values may be returned. These could be literal text content of a meta element, a resource identifier (e.g. a url defined by the href attribute value), and/or recursively nested meta annotations or other xml. This method returns all of these.

property -
Returns:
